<HEADLINE> Ugandan Organization Lauded for Fighting Poverty </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Ugandan President Yoweri
Museveni has commended members of Lugoba Waste Management and
Economic Enterprise Development Community for the good job they
are doing in fighting poverty.
</P>
<P>
The president made the remarks in Kawempe division of Kampala
district Monday, a press release from the President's Office
said.
</P>
<P>
The group is a comunity based organization made up of 58 women
and youths united to conserve and protect the environment. It is
engaged in fish farming at Lugoba, Kampala district.
</P>
<P>
Museveni said that their project will greatly supplement the
government's struggle for eradicating poverty in the country.
</P>
<P>
He promised the government assistance, particularly in feeding
the fish to maturity stage.
</P>
<P>
The group is an affiliation of an indigenous non-governmental
organization called "The Uganda Environmental Protection Forum".
It also trains people in fruit tree grafting.
</P>
<P>
It now has a fish pond of 30 meters by 29 meters. The group
earns over 40 million shillings (40,000 U.S. Dollars) per year.
</P>
<P>
Apart from fish farming, members are also engaged, on
individual basis, in other income-earning projects like animal
husbandry and horticulture. 
</P>
</TEXT>
