<HEADLINE> Russia, India Sign Seven Agreements </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia and India signed
seven agreements here Monday evening following wide-ranging talks
between visiting Russian Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov and
Indian Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee.
</P>
<P>
Primakov, who arrived here for a two-day official visit to New
Delhi, and Vajpayee were present at the signing ceremony.
</P>
<P>
The Long-term Agreement on Military-Technical Cooperation upto
the Year 2010 marked the high point of Primakov's visit, the first
head of government of one of the permanent members of the UN
Security Council to visit New Delhi following India's nuclear
tests last May.
</P>
<P>
Other agreements included the Agreements on Mutual Legal
Assistance in Criminal Matters, Extradition, Joint Document on
Development of Trade, Economic, Industrial, Financial, Science and
Technology Cooperation, Air Transport, Cooperation in the Field of
Communications and a consular convention.
</P>
<P>
During a Brief press conference after the ceremony, the Russian
Prime Minister said that he discussed with his Indian counterpart
wide-ranging issues including bilateral, regional and
international relations and cooperations.
</P>
<P>
Asked if Russian support India to be a member of the Security
Council, Primakov said that India is strong and appropriated to be
a candidate to occupy a position in the Security Council.
</P>
<P>
The Russian leader and his delegation is scheduled to end the
visit Tuesday morning and leave for home in the afternoon.
</P>
</TEXT>
