<HEADLINE> German Export Loses Growth Momentum </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BONN, December 21 (Xinhua) -- As a result of the crises in
Asia, Latin America and Russia, German exports growth lost
momentum in the third quarter of this year, the Federal Statistics
Office reported Monday.
</P>
<P>
A report of the german Statistics Office said, that the German
exports in the third quarter were 3.1 per cent higher compared
with the same period of 1997.
</P>
<P>
But the German exports in the first quarter this year had been
15.9 per cent higher and in the second quarter, 10.0 per cent over
exports of the same quarters last year, the report showed.
</P>
<P>
German exports to Russia in the July-September came to 2.1
billion dollars, down 26.6 per cent from the third-quarter 1997
period, according to the office report. And the Exports to Japan
were down by 12 per cent to 2.7 billion dollars in the third
quarter.  
</P>
</TEXT>
