<HEADLINE> Turkey Welcomes End of Attacks against Iraq </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Turkey said on Monday it
welcomes the end of the four nights of air strikes against Iraq,
but is deeply concerned about the death toll in Iraq.
</P>
<P>
The Turkish Foreign Ministry said in a statement that
Turkey attaches great importance to the protection of territorial
integrity of Iraq, while Iraq must fully comply with the
resolutions of the United Nations Security Council.
</P>
<P>
Turkey believes that Iraq, which is an important country of
the international society, should gain its place again, said the
foreign ministry.
</P>
<P>
It added that Turkey will continue to increase consultations
with all the countries concerned on this issue. 
</P>
