Chissano said he was encouraged by the prospects of peace in the
country, adding "We appreciate that an immediate ceasefire was
agreed at the African-French summit in Paris by all parties of the
conflict, which opens up a real possibility to the comprehensive
resolution to the conflicts in the Great Lakes region."
</P>
<P>
Regarding the domestic situation, the president said
Mozambique is politically stable with its people participating
more and more in the country's democratic life.
</P>
<P>
Meanwhile, said the president, despite its crippling foreign
debt, the economic growth in Mozambique continues its encouraging
trend and is expected to reach 11.2 percent this year. 
