<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Jiang Calls on the Public to Study Hard </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Jiang Zemin, general secretary
of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central Committee, urged
people to study hard during a visit to the National Library in
Beijing today.
</P>
<P>
He was accompanied by Li Lanqing, a Standing Committee member
of the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, and Zeng
Qinghong, alternate member of the Political Bureau and member of
the Secretariat of the CPC Central Committee.
</P>
<P>
During his tour, Jiang was given an introduction about the
library by Zhou Heping, deputy director of the library, and
exchanged opinions with readers on such topics as education,
economics, sciences and the law.
</P>
<P>
As China's state library, the NLB grew out of the Capital
Library, which was founded in 1909. With a floor space of 170,000
square meters, the library is the fourth biggest in the world and
the No.1 in Asia.
</P>
<P>
The library provides services to its readers throughout the
year and is visited by more than 8,000 people everyday. 
</P>
</TEXT>
