<HEADLINE> 2 Killed in Clashes over Land in Somalia </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MOGADISHU, December 22 (Xinhua) -- At least two men were
killed and more than 15 others wounded when armed clashes broke
out between the two sides in south Mogadishu Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
According to eyewitnesses, heavy gun fire exchanged between
militiamen from the Islamic court of Shirkole of south Mogadishu
and clan-motivated militiamen near the busy intersection of Bar
Ubah.
</P>
<P>
The reason for the fighting is not known officially. However,
the eyewitnesses in the area said the shooting began after a
serious dispute had erupted between a man driving a truck with 10
armed militiamen and another whom they had quarreled over the
ownership of a piece of land at Aymiska area of south Mogadishu.
</P>
<P>
The man with the truck has tried to kidnap the other man
before the Islamic court militiamen of Shirkole intervened, they
said.
</P>
<P>
The eyewitnesses said that three of the Islamic militiamen
were wounded during the early moments of the clash.
</P>
<P>
However, the Islamist forces have in the end managed to
control the situation and forcefully restored the security in the
area after the militiamen from the other side fled for their
lives, leaving behind one dead and two others wounded.
</P>
<P>
Officials from the Islamic court said the case of the two
sides over the dispute of the land ownership will soon be revised
after the civil courts of the late regime could not handle the
long-standing dispute between the two sides. 
</P>
