<HEADLINE> 6 Nigerian Officers Promoted </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LAGOS, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Nigerian military leader
General Abdulsalam Abubakar has promoted six officers from the
rank of major generals to that of lieutenant generals, or
three-star generals.
</P>
<P>
Speaking to Xinhua here Tuesday, Defense spokesman Colonel
S.A. Tella said there is nothing special about the promotion,
adding that it is just fulfillment of vacancy.
</P>
<P>
According to a statement Monday from the office of the
Principal Staff Officer to Abubakar, the Chief of General Staff,
Rear Admiral Mike Akgihbe is now a Vice Admiral, while the Chief
of Defense Staff, Air Vice-Marshal Al-Amin Daggash is now an Air
Marshal.
</P>
<P>
The Chief of Army Staff, Major-General Ishaya Bamaiyi was
promoted to rank of Lieutenant General; the Chief of Naval Staff,
Rear Admiral Jubrila Ayinla to the rank of Vice Admiral.
</P>
<P>
Also affected in the promotion exercise are the Chief of Air
Staff, Air Vice-Marshal Nsikak Eduok and Major-General Rufus
Kupolati, Chairman of the Petroleum Trust Fund for the Armed
Forces and Police.
</P>
<P>
Before Abubakar took the office in June, Nigeria had only
three lieutenant generals, including former Chief of General
Staff, Oladipo Diya, Minister of the Federal Capital Territory,
Jeremiah Useni and Industry Minister Balarabe Haladu.
</P>
<P>
All the service chiefs then, including Abubakar himself, who
was the Chief Defense Staff, were at the rank of major generals.
</P>
<P>
Diya is serving a jail term for alleged involvement in a coup
plot against late head of state General Sani Abacha. Useni
retired from the army soon after Abubakar came to power, while
Haladu died in the mid-year.
</P>
<P>
Abubakar was promoted to the rank of general when he was
chosen by the military as the new leader, following the sudden
death of Abacha in June. 
</P>
</TEXT>
