<HEADLINE> Anglo-American Co. Buys Zambia Mines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LUSAKA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Anglo-American Corporation
(AAC) and Zambia have signed a non-legally binding memorandum of
understanding over the sale of Nchanga, Nkana and Konkola mines,
AAC said here Monday.
</P>
<P>
Zambia Daily Mail Tuesday quoted an AAC spokesman as saying
that The memorandum will only become effective when the two sides
sign it.
</P>
<P>
He indicated that at this stage AAC is concerned with
depressed metal prices and the firm may not meet the immediate
cash requirements of the transaction.
</P>
<P>
