U.S. Dollars and the new owner are expected to take them over by
the end of March of next year, Finance Minister Edith Nawakwi
said last week.
</P>
<P>
In may this year donors pledged to give Zambia an aid of 530
million Dollars. However, they have withheld the money to
pressure it to speed up the privatization of the Zambia
Consolidated Copper Mines (ZCCM).
</P>
<P>
Due to disagreement over the cost of Nkana and Nchanga mines,
Zambia discontinued the negotiations with Kafue Consortium last
April over the sale of the two biggest mines in the country.
</P>
<P>
It was reported earlier that originally Zambia demanded Kafue
pay 400 million Dollars for the two mines. 
