<DOCNO> XIE19981222.0106 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Yearender: Preparations for Macao SAR Well Under Way (Part 1) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Since its founding on May 5 this
year, the Preparatory Committee for the Macao Special Administrative
Region (SAR) has been operating well to work out a series of decisions
on establishing the future SAR.
</P>
<P>
Being a subordinate organ under China's National People's Congress,
the Preparatory Committee mainly takes charge of mapping out the
methods on forming the first administrative, legislative and judicial
bodies of the Macao SAR. And it has to handle various legal, economic,
social and cultural affairs concerning the handover.
</P>
<P>
In particular, the Preparatory Committee will organize a 200-member
election committee consisting of only Macao residents who will elect
the first chief executive of the Macao SAR.
</P>
<P>
With conscientious, responsible and pragmatic spirit, the 100
members of the committee, 60 of whom are Macao residents, have been
collecting the opinons and suggestions of local people on
constructing the SAR.
</P>
<P>
From September 3 to 6, the Preparatory Committee held 13
consultation meetings in Macao to solicit the opinions of local people
on forming the election committee. A total of 324 organizations of
varied walks of life and nearly 1,000 persons took part in the
meetings.
</P>
<P>
With enthusiastic participation, Macao residents voiced their views
on the principles reigning over the election committee, qualifications
of the committee members and the procedures to set up the committee.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981222.0107 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Preparations for Macao SAR Well Under Way (Part 2) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Based on the consultations, the Fourth Plenary Session of the
Preparatory Committee in early November passed the method on forming
the election committee.
</P>
<P>
The method stipulates that any Macao permanent resident over 18-
years-old can apply to join the election committee provided that they
support the "one country, two systems" concept and the Macao Basic
Law. The number of candidates for election committee will be 30
percent more than the actual figure of committee members.
</P>
<P>
What's important, the method makes it clear that the procedures to
turn out the election committee must follow the principle of equity,
justness, transparancy, democracy and honesty in response to the
expectation of Macao residents.
</P>
<P>
Accordingly, election committee members are supposed not to accept
bribes, influence the stance of other members or utter remarks of
personal attack.
</P>
<P>
The election of the chief executive of the Macao SAR indicates that
Macao residents, who have been under colonial rule for more than 400
years with the governor appointed from Portugal, will be ushered in a
new period featuring democratic participation in political affairs.
</P>
<P>
In addition to the method on forming the election committee, the
Preparatory Committee has made a series of significant decisions in
its four plenary sessions from May to November.
</P>
<P>
The decision that China's central government will station troops in
the Macao SAR has been hailed by the masses of Macao residents who
think that the troops will play a frightening role for containing gang
crimes in Macao.
</P>
<P>
Qian Qichen, chairman of the Preparatory Committee, explained that
the stationing of troops symbolizes China's sovereignty over Macao,
the troops will take charge of only defense affairs and the central
government will pay relevant military expenses.
</P>
<P>
To localize civil servants has been a major issue in the
transitional period, for most senior employees of the Macao government
used to be Portuguese. But up to now, local Chinese still make up only
a small part of government department directors, the highest rank of
civil service in Macao.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981222.0108 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Preparations for Macao SAR Well Under Way (Part 3) </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
In this sense, the Preparatory Committee has vehemently urged
the Portuguese Macao government to quicken the pace of localizing
civil servants and raising their competence.
</P>
<P>
With regard to Macao's public security, the Preparatory Committee
has made a decision requiring that the Macao government shoulder full
responsibility for improving public security and step up the crackdown
upon criminal activities so as to ensure steady handover.
</P>
<P>
Considering that the SAR government will be established on December
20 of 1999, the Preparatory Committee has decided that the Portuguese
side should cooperate with the Chinese side in mapping out the fiscal
budget for the year 2000 so that economic and fiscal policies after
the handover can be implemented well.
</P>
<P>
With hundreds of years of Portuguese rule, there are a large
number of Macao-born Portuguese in Macao. Now that China defies
double nationality, the Preparatory Committee decides that
Macao-born Portuguese can opt for Chinese or Portuguese
nationalities. They can remain residents of the SAR before they
make a choice.
</P>
<P>
To make the future SAR government more clean, the Preparatory
Committee has decided in its third plenary session that
anti-corruption and auditing organs and an independent customs should
be established.
</P>
<P>
In terms of pension fund for retired civil servants of the
Portuguese Macao government, the Preparatory Committee has called for
the Macao government to cease transferring more pension fund to
Portugal before a consensus is reached in the Sino-Portuguse Joint
Liaison Group.
</P>
<P>
In addition, the Preparatory Committee has made resolutions on the
issuance of stamps during the transitional period and after the
handover, and on holiday arrangements in 2000.
</P>
<P>
Next year, the Preparatory Committee is expected to hold
another five plenary sessions on some key issues. The most
important one is to work out the method on electing the first
chief executive. The method may be approved at the fifth plenum in
January.
</P>
<P>
With reference to the practice in establishing the Hong Kong SAR,
the first chief executive of the Macao SAR should be elected half year
before the handover, which means the end of May or early June.
</P>
<P>
Other major works of the Preparatory Committee include further
research on the administrative framework of the SAR, the checking on
current laws in Macao, the transfer of assets of the Portuguese Macao
government and celebrating activities around the handover. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981222.0109 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-22 13:45 </DATE_TIME>
