<HEADLINE> China Issues 1.6 Billion Yuan in Railway Construction Bonds </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- On Thursday, China will issue
1.6 billion yuan worth of corporate bonds to finance the country's
railway projects.
</P>
<P>
With an annual interest rate of 6.95 percent, the bonds will
mature in 2003. The China Securities Co. Ltd. will be the major
underwriter for the bond issue, which has been granted a AAA
rating.
</P>
<P>
Funds raised through the bond issue will be used for the
country's key railway projects, whose total investment exceeds 20
billion yuan, and will all be completed before 2000, said
officials with the Ministry of Railways, issuer of the bonds.
</P>
<P>
Since 1995, China has raised nearly ten billion yuan by issuing
corporate bonds. This issue is the second this year, the first
having raised 2.1 billion yuan in the first half.
</P>
<P>
A ranking official with the Ministry of Railways said the
ministry is planning more bond issues because a total of 250
billion yuan will be needed for railway construction in the next
five years.  
</P>
</TEXT>
