<HEADLINE> Marxist Scholar Acclaimed </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Top Chinese officials
including Li Ruihuan, a Standing Committee member of the Political
Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, today attended a forum
celebrating 'The Complete Works of Hu Sheng', a renowned Marxist
scholar.
</P>
<P>
Li offered his congratulations to the author, saying that Hu is
a respected philosopher, historian, and one of the few erudite and
accomplished Party theoreticians.
</P>
<P>
Li, also chairman of the National Committee of the Chinese
People's Political Consultative Conference, said that Hu has
devoted himself to theoretical research on Marxism and contributed
greatly to the publicizing and interpretation of Mao Zedong
Thought and Deng Xiaoping Theory.
</P>
<P>
The book, comprising six volumes and some three million
characters, has been compiled by Hu Sheng himself. More than 100
experts and scholars from Beijing's academic circles attended
the forum. 
