<TEXT>
<P>
PARIS, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Laurent Perpere was appointed
as the new Paris St Germain president, replacing Charles Bietry,
who quit on Monday after less than six months in the job.
according to reports on Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
PSG, one of the wealthiest clubs in France, was beaten 0-2 by
lowly Lorient on Saturday and is 11th, 10 points from the bottom.
</P>
<P>
Perpere is the club's finance director. Bietry, formerly head
of sports at Canal Plus, replaced Michel Denisot last July with
the aim of winning the French title five years after the last
success in 1994, reports said.
</P>
<P>
Last October, Bietry decided to sack coach Alain Giresse after
the club was eliminated by Israel's Maccabi Haifa in the first
round of the European Cup Winners' Cup and managed to score only
six goals in eight league games.
</P>
<P>
New trainer Artur Jorge, who led PSG to its last league title
in 1994, also failed to take the club back on the winning track.
</P>
