<HEADLINE> Passenger Arrivals to Macao Decrease in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Passenger arrivals to Macao by means
of marine, land and air routes were 551,516 in October this year,
decreasing 3.5 percent from the same month of 1997, latest official
statistics show.
</P>
<P>
According to figures released by the Macao Census and Statistics
Department, the number of passengers to Macao from January to October
went down 2.1 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the ten months, passenger arrivals from China's mainland
areas and Hong Kong accounted for 75.9 percent of the total, resulting
in an increase of 6.6 percent over the same period last year.
</P>
<P>
However, those coming from the Republic of Korea, Japan, and
southeast and south Asian countries decreased 77.3 percent, 46.4
percent, 37.6 percent and 24 percent. 
</P>
