<HEADLINE> Macao Consumer Price Index in November Down Slightly </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MACAO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The composite consumer price index
for November in Macao decreased 0.3 percent from October, latest
figures from the Macao Census and Statistics Department show.
</P>
<P>
According to the figures, the cost of food, soft drinks, transport,
telecommunications, education and recreation went down slightly while
the cost of clothing and daily necessities rose a little bit.
</P>
<P>
In comparison with November last year, the price index decreased
1.5 percent.
</P>
<P>
During the first 11 months this year, the average composite
consumer price index increased 0.4 percent over the same period of
1997.  
