<HEADLINE> Hong Kong's Retail Sales Down in October </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
HONG KONG, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The value of total retail
sales in October this year decreased by 20 percent to 15.8 billion
HK dollars (2.26 billion U.S. dollars) compared with the same
period of last year.
</P>
<P>
The newly released government statistics show that sales of
motor vehicles declined the most, by 49 percent in value or 43
percent in volume in October this year.
</P>
<P>
This was followed by sales of commodities in department stores,
clothing and footwear, miscellaneous consumer goods, fuels,
jewelry, watches and consumer durable goods.
</P>
<P>
Sales of food, alcoholic drinks and tobacco remained virtually
unchanged in both value and volume and that of commodities in
supermarkets increased by 5 percent in value, but remained
virtually unchanged in volume, the Census and Statistics
Department said.
</P>
<P>
A government Secretariat spokesman noted that retail business
remained week in the month, as consumer sentiment was still
dampened by the uncertain economic outlook and slackened labor
market conditions. 
</P>
</TEXT>
