<HEADLINE> South China City to Improve Investment Environment </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
GUANGZHOU, December 22 (Xinhua) -- This capital of south China's
Guangdong Province today announced regulations to improve its
investment environment.
</P>
<P>
The regulations, consisting of eight parts and 34 articles,
call for an end to levying illegal tolls and fines on enterprises
so as to lighten their financial burdens.
</P>
<P>
Under the new regulations, the legal rights and interests of
foreign businesses will be fully protected, and law suits involving
foreign business people will receive prompt and fair investigations
and hearings.
</P>
<P>
The regulations pledge an open, fair and just competitive
environment for both domestic and overseas enterprises, and
welcome the latter to participate in the restructuring and
reorganizing of state-owned enterprises.
</P>
<P>
These regulations became effective today. 
</P>
</TEXT>
