<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Unemployment Rate Increases in Philippines </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MANILA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The unemployment rate in the
Philippines increased to 9.6 percent in October from 7.9 percent a
year ago, the National Statistics Office said here Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
"Labor force (in October this year) was 1.013 million more than
in October 1997, with 374,000 finding work bringing the number of
unemployed to 639,000 and the unemployment rate to 9.6 percent,"
the office said in a labor force survey.
</P>
<P>
However, the office said, October's unemployment rate dropped
from 13.3 percent in April, the highest in the past few years.
</P>
<P>
The office also said employment in service in October gained
4.8 percent over that of October 1997 while that in agriculture
was slightly over the level a year ago.
</P>
<P>
Employment in industry declined by 4.7 percent in the month
from that of a year ago, it added.
</P>
<P>
Economists here blamed the on-going financial crisis for the
high unemployment rate in the country, where many companies closed
or have cut their staff since the crisis started 18 months ago.
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
