<BODY>
<HEADLINE> High-Profile Tamil Rebel Cadre Arrested in Colombo </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan police have
arrested the leader of the Colombo intelligence wing of the
Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE), an evening newspaper here
reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The Observer quoted police as saying the suspect, identified as
Yogeswaran Nixon, has been known in the LTTE circles by the code
name of Sandran.
</P>
<P>
Investigations have revealed that Sandran had been planning
massive destruction in Colombo, the country's capital, a senior
security official said.
</P>
<P>
On interrogation Sandran had confessed that he was the leader
of the LTTE's Colombo finance and intelligence division. He came
to Colombo from Jaffna in 1990 and was living with his parents in
the city, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Police said Sandran had been an active member in the LTTE's
Colombo activities since arriving in the capital, working on
instructions from the LTTE.
</P>
<P>
It has also been found that the suspect had been responsible
for providing bombs, suicide kits, money and cyanide capsules to
other LTTE cadres who came to Colombo on killing and destruction
missions, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
Sandran joined the LTTE in 1988 and had received special
training in handling artillery, the reports added.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE rebels have been waging a war against the government
since 1983 for a separate Tamil state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
