<HEADLINE> First Palestinian Airliner Lands at Cairo Airport </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
CAIRO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The first Palestinian passenger
plane landed Tuesday at Cairo international airport, marking the
launching of a regular flight between Gaza and the Egyptian
capital.
</P>
<P>
Egyptian Minister of Transport and Communications Soliman
Metwalli Soliman welcomed the maiden Palestinian flight with 14
passengers on the plane, Egypt's Middle East News Agency reported.
</P>
<P>
Soliman said the operation of the new flight route emphasizes
the Palestinians' sovereignty over "the land and airport of
Palestine."
</P>
<P>
He expressed hope that the Palestinian planes would reach the
airports all over the world.
</P>
<P>
