biweekly flight to the newly operated Gaza airport, which was
opened on November 24 under the Wye River peace agreement between
the Palestinians and Israel.
</P>
<P>
Upon arrival, head of the Palestinian Aviation Authority Fayez
Zeedan said that he was happy the first Palestinian airliner
landed at Cairo international airport.
</P>
<P>
"The operation of this regular route embodies the distinguished
and close ties between the two brotherly peoples, and enhances the
eventful and inspiring record of support offered by the Egyptian
people to the Palestinian people," Zeedan said.
</P>
<P>
He spoke highly of Egypt's key role in training Palestinian
aviation technicians and operators. 
