<HEADLINE> Three Chinese Companies' Trade Permits Revoked </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- China's Ministry of Foreign
Trade and Economic Cooperation (MOFTEC) has revoked the trade
permits of three companies responsible for exchange infractions, a
ministry source said today.
</P>
<P>
One company under MOFTEC and one under the State Family
Planning Commission had their import-export rights cancelled,
while the other one, under the State Administration of Internal
Trade, was forbidden to contract for imports and foreign labor
services.
</P>
<P>
MOFTEC said this was the most severe administrative punishment
ever adopted by the ministry.
</P>
<P>
The State Council has ordered stricter administration in order
to prevent exchange infractions.
</P>
<P>
MOFTEC warned enterprises with import and export rights to draw
a lesson from this incident and avoid illegal dealings in foreign
exchange.
</P>
<P>
The ministry said that if enterprises are verified to be
involved in smuggling or exchange infractions, MOFTEC will issue
warnings or revoke their trade permits.  
</P>
</TEXT>
