<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Changed Course of British Hot Balloon "Unacceptable": FM Spokesman </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- China regrets that the British
balloon Challenge has violated the agreement reached between China
and Britain for its flight over Chinese air space.
</P>
<P>
Chinese Foreign Ministry spokesman Zhu Bangzao made this remark
at today's regular news briefing in response to questions on the
matter.
</P>
<P>
According to Zhu, "China has decided to disapprove the entry of
the balloon into Chinese air space after taking into consideration
the safety of the hot balloon and civil aviation."
</P>
<P>
Zhu indicated that on November 17, the British embassy in China
issued a written guarantee in which it said that the balloon will
fly along an agreed course over China.
</P>
<P>
"The Chinese side will not take responsibility for the outcome
of such an act in violation of the agreement," he noted.
</P>
<P>
He said that China takes "an active attitude" for hot-balloon
activities and has approved the entry of three British-registered
hot balloons, including Challenge, into China's territorial
space. "However, it is international practice to require that such
activities be carried out under related regulations," he pointed
out.
</P>
<P>
"I don't know the specific position of the balloon, so I can
only tell you about developments in the matter later, via
convenient channels," he said.  
</P>
</TEXT>
