<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Stocks Edge Up on Singapore Market </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
SINGAPORE, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Boosted by the overnight
resilience on Wall Street and speculation of lower interest rate,
Share prices edged up on Singapore Stock Market Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
The benchmark Straits Times Index (STI) gained 14.67 points to
end at 1,412.40. Nonetheless, the key STI finished losing grip on
the intra-day high of 1,419.93 points.
</P>
<P>
The total turnover increased to 141.17 million units worth
285.96 million Singapore dollars (about 172.96 million U.S.
dollars). Falls outnumbered rises by 140 to 105 with 174 counters
unchanged.
</P>
<P>
DBS Land remained at the top of the actives chart of the day
with a turnover of 15.29 million units. ST Cap was the second most
heavily traded stock with a volume of 6.26 million units done. Van
DH was next with 5.68 million counters changing hands.
</P>
<P>
DBS F still headed the ascent of the day with a jump of 120
cents to 15.70 Singapore dollars. SPH 100 was up 60 cents to
finish at 18.40 Singapore dollars. DBS gained 30 cents to end at
8.20 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
On the downside, Creative 50 remained the top loser of the day
with a decline of 90 cents to 23.60 Singapore dollars. Elec&AMP;E was
next slipping by 35 cents to close at 5.10 U.S. dollars. Venture
retreated 30 cents to end at 6.10 Singapore dollars.
</P>
<P>
Dealers noted that blue chips continued to find favor and
appeared more bullish on overnight Wall Street's rally and
speculation over further interest rate cuts.
</P>
<P>
The market held steady throughout the session though it closed
off its intra-day highs and falling counters outnumbered advances,
they said. 
</P>
</TEXT>
