<TEXT>
<P>
NEW DELHI, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Russia and India signed
seven agreements here Monday evening following wide-ranging talks
between visiting Russian Prime Minister Yevgeny Primakov and
Indian Prime Minister Atal Behari Vajpayee.
</P>
<P>
The Long-Term Agreement on Military-Technical Cooperation up to
the year 2010, along with another six agreements on various
issues, highlighted Primakov's visit.
</P>
<P>
