permanent members of the United Nations Security Council and also
the five nuclear powers after India's nuclear tests in May.
</P>
<P>
Primakov told a press conference that Russian President Boris
Yeltsin, who cancelled his December visit to New Delhi, would
visit the country sometimes next year.
</P>
<P>
Yeltsin's visit would give a major thrust to strategic
partnership between Moscow and New Delhi, he added. 
