<HEADLINE> Sri Lankan Troops Kill 34 Tamil Rebels </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Sri Lankan government troops
Monday killed 34 Tamil rebels in Northern Province of the country,
a military spokesman said here Tuesday afternoon.
</P>
<P>
Spokesman Ink Dewage said government troops on ambush engaged a
tractor coupled with three trailers with machine guns, rocket
propelled grenades and mines. The tractor was carrying about 50
rebels. The troops confirmed over 30 Tamil rebels were killed.
</P>
<P>
In another incident in general area Karapaddamurippu on the
same day, troops sniped and killed two terrorist.
</P>
<P>
Government troops observed a terrorist movement and engaged
with small arms Monday in general area north of Kanakarayankulam,
killing two rebels, said Dewage, adding that subsequently troops
recovered the two dead bodies along with their weapons.
</P>
<P>
Also on Monday at Eraur area, Tamil rebels threw two hand
grenades at a bus in the army convoy plying from Batticaloa to
Welikanda. One soldier was killed and eight others injured in the
incident, Dewage added.
</P>
<P>
The Tamil rebels have been fighting a 15-year war against the
government for a separate state in the north and east of the
country. 
</P>
</TEXT>
