<HEADLINE> Sino-Italian-Financed Auto Project in East China </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
Nanjing, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Construction of the East China
Teksid Automobile Casting Co. Ltd. began recently in the city of
Zhenjiang in Jiangsu Province.
</P>
<P>
The project, the largest of its kind in China's automobile
industry, is jointly financed by the Yuejin Automobile Group
Company, the Shanghai Automobile Industry (Group) Corporation, and
Teksid Co. Ltd. of Italy, at a cost of 80.88 million U.S. dollars.
</P>
<P>
According to local sources, Chinese investors and their Italian
partner will share the investment equally. The cooperative term of the
joint venture is 30 years.
</P>
<P>
When completed, the new company will manufacture about 990,000
units of automobile cylinders annually with the use of advanced
production technology and management expertise from Italy.
</P>
<P>
China has long depended on imports for auto engine cylinders,
and the new company will reduce this dependence, said observers
here.  
</P>
