<HEADLINE> Uganda to Have First Heart Hospital </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KAMPALA, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Construction work has begun
to transform a Kampala-based hospital's Children's Ward into a
modern theater for open heart surgery, the first of its kind in
Uganda.
</P>
<P>
The project, expected to be inaugurated in May 1999, can be
used to handle all types of heart problems, including open and
closed operations, the New Vision daily reported Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
Project director Lawrence Kaggwa told Kampala City Council
officials on a Christmas tour Monday that open heart surgery will
be carried out in the Mulago hospital for the first time.
</P>
<P>
A total of 28 million U.S. Dollars from both the Ugandan
government and the African Development Bank is expected to be
spent on the project, he added.
</P>
<P>
Rehabilitation includes the general overhaul of the block
facilities, including fixing the heart equipment and changing the
sewerage system.
</P>
<P>
So far patients with chronic heart problems have always had to
be flown abroad for operation while simple heart surgery was done
at Mulago, the national referral hospital. 
</P>
