<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-22 </DATE_TIME>
<BODY>
<HEADLINE> China Active in Absorbing Overseas Talent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- China has been absorbing a
wide range of talent in many fields through a variety of channels
over the past several years, according to Wan Xueyuan, director of
the State Administration of Foreign Expert Affairs, adding that
this foreign expertise has given strong impetus to the nation's
economic and social progress.
</P>
<P>
Statistics show that China has brought 170,000 foreign experts to
work in China over the past two years, raising the total number of
such people to 660,000 since China introduced reforms and opening
20 years ago.
</P>
<P>
Foreign experts are involved in such fields
as finance and insurance, and medical and legal services, in addition
to the traditional areas of industry, agriculture and educational and
research institutions.
</P>
<P>
During the past two years, overseas talent in industrial
sectors has helped realize over 120 achievements in technical
renovation and exploration of new products; while in agricultural,
more than 270 fine new varieties of floral have been introduced.
</P>
<P>
However, Wan also pointed out that problems exist with the
absorption of overseas talent. For example, a mechanism for
spreading the experience gained from the introduction of foreign
talent has not yet formed, and of this talent is redundant,
leading to poor efficiency.
</P>
<P>
Speaking of the introduction of overseas talent in the next two
years, Wan noted that these people will work mainly to improve
agriculture, deepen state-owned-enterprise reforms, and promote
development in central and western China. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
