<HEADLINE> Local Official Sentenced to Life Imprisonment for Taking Bribes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NANCHANG, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The People's Intermediate
Court of Nanchang, capital of east China's Jiangxi Province, on
Monday sentenced Gu Sanfu, former deputy director of the
provincial grain reserve bureau, to life imprisonment for taking
bribes.
</P>
<P>
Gu was also deprived of political rights for life and had
property worth 100,000 yuan (about 12,000 U.S. dollars)
confiscated, in addition to repaying bribes exceeding 378,900 yuan
and other unidentified property worth more than 785,000 yuan.
</P>
<P>
An investigation showed that Gu took bribes many times in
exchange for illicit favors related to grain distribution quotas
and rail transportation when he served as deputy director of the
provincial grain reserve bureau from early 1993 to early 1996.
