<HEADLINE> Chinese Consumers Still Prefer Domestic Brands </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- Quality-conscious Chinese
consumers are more likely to buy domestic goods than foreign
products, according to a recent national survey.
</P>
<P>
Today's Economic Daily reports that the survey by China Central
Television Station (CCTV) found that 35 of the 60 best-selling
name brand products are Chinese brands.
</P>
<P>
The survey was of 16,461 types of foodstuff, beverages,
cigarettes, garments, cosmetics, and electronics,
telecommunications, and transportation items and 9,200 people in
34 major Chinese cities.
</P>
<P>
According to the paper, the results indicate that Chinese
consumers are becoming more mature in choosing and are demanding
not only high quality and reasonable prices, but also convenience
and good after-sale service.
</P>
<P>
It also shows that most consumers think that quality is more
important than price and popularity.
</P>
<P>
However, buyers of durable goods are more likely to be
influenced by advertisements and the reommendation of friends and
relatives. 
</P>
