<HEADLINE> Beijing Protecting Drinking Water Sources </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese capital is going
to spend 39 million yuan improving the environment around Miyun
Reservoir, which supplies about half the city's drinking water.
</P>
<P>
The money will come from government funds and a bond issue.
</P>
<P>
Currently, 5.72 million tons of sand and dust enter the
reservoir each year, threatening the reservoir's capacity and its
water quality.
</P>
<P>
The project will deal concern a 280-sq.km. area, where grass
and trees will be planted and engineering projects carried out. It
is expected to be finished before next October.  
</P>
