<HEADLINE> Chinese Peace, Disarmament Association Convenes in Beijing </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BEIJING, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The Chinese People's
Association for Peace and Disarmament (CPAPD) convened here today
to review its work over the past three years.
</P>
<P>
CPAPD president He Luli, also vice-chairwoman of the Chinese
National People's Congress (NPC) Standing Committee, delivered the
meeting's opening address.
</P>
<P>
The committee's vice-chairmen Wu Jieping and Zhou Guangzhao,
together with vice-chairmen of the National Committee of the
Chinese People's Political Consultative Conference Zhao Puchu and
Ding Guangxun, were elected honorary presidents of the CPAPD.
</P>
<P>
Zhou Guangzhao, and Dai Bingguo, head of the International
Department of the Communist Party of China (CPC) Central
Committee, as well as representatives from 25 CPAPD member groups
also attended.
</P>
<P>
Founded in June 1985 as an unofficial organization for
promoting peace, the CPAPD has devoted itself to international
communications and academic exchanges for mutual understanding,
friendship and peace.
</P>
<P>
The CPAPD has now set up relations with more than 300 peace
organizations in over 90 countries, and dozens of international
organizations, including the United Nations. It also sponsored the
10th International Week of Science and Peace in China. 
</P>
