<HEADLINE> Experts Forecast 3 Percent Economic Increase for Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Portugal's economy is expected
to grow at a rate of 3 percent in 1999, according to a survey
report of some Portuguese financial experts.
</P>
<P>
The report added that the growth of the domestic demand and
lower interest rate will become the two major factors supporting
the development of the national economy.
</P>
<P>
Owing to a rise of four to 4.5 percentage in domestic demand in
1998, the import and export of the country have increased 13.5
percent and 10.25 percent, respectively, the report said.
</P>
<P>
But it said that in 1999 the export of Portugal will grow at a
lower speed of 4 percent because of a decline in consumers'
confidence and weak domestic demand. 
</P>
</TEXT>
