<HEADLINE> Mexican Government Warns Citizens of Volcano Ashes </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
MEXICO CITY, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Falling ashes from
Popocatepetl volcano, 50 miles away from Mexico City, have
prompted local authorities to urge Monday residents to take
special safety measures.
</P>
<P>
Mexico City's civil protection direction called on the
residents not to wear contact lenses and to have their arms and
legs covered to protect their nose and mouth.
</P>
<P>
Residents were warned to keep doors and windows shut and to
protect water supplies. They were also requested to collect the
ashes into plastic bags.
</P>
<P>
From Sunday ashes spewed by the giant volcano have been raining
on at least 6 of the city's 116 districts, leading to the
suspension of airport activities.
</P>
<P>
The volcano's gush has caused continuous tremors and spouted
much ashes for five times since last Saturday, and the yellow
warning lamps for villagers in the mountain still remained turned
on, said an official source. 
</P>
