<HEADLINE> Elderly Population Rises Sharply in Portugal </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LISBON, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The number of elderly people in
Portugal has been rising quickly, according to a report by the
national statistics bureau.
</P>
<P>
The report said that the number of people over the age of 65
had risen to 1.5 million in 1997, accounting for 15.1 percent of
the total population. The figure in 1990 was only 1.3 million.
</P>
<P>
The report attributed the increase to the low birth rate and
increasing longevity.
</P>
<P>
However, it said, that only 16 percent of the over-65s were
healthy, far below the European average. This had much to do with
the high percentage of people who drank and smoked in Portugal,
the report added. 
</P>
