<HEADLINE> Sri Lanka's Rebel Chief Orders Arrest of Area Leader </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
COLOMBO, December 22 (Xinhua) -- The Mullaitivu area leader of
the Liberation Tigers of Tamil Eelam (LTTE) and three other cadres
close to him have been arrested on the orders of LTTE leader
Velupillai Prabhakaran, according to reports reaching here
Tuesday.
</P>
<P>
They had been taken into custody by the Tigers at Mulliyawalai,
northeast of Sri Lanka, last Sunday for defying Prabhakaran's
orders, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The Mullaitivu leader had refused to hand over a consignment of
weapons to a LTTE activist named by the Tiger leader and instead
given the stock to another group, the reports said.
</P>
<P>
The arrested rebel cadres were also charged with the misuse of
weapons and a gross violation of specific orders laid down by the
LTTE leader.
</P>
<P>
They have reportedly been taken to a torture chamber in a LTTE
camp in Mallaitivu.
</P>
<P>
Observers here say that the arrest of the Mallaitivu leader
indicates a growing division within the ranks of the LTTE and a
turning point in the scenario of LTTE operations as he had played
an active role in Mullaitivu, the domain of LTTE activity.
</P>
<P>
The LTTE has been fighting a war against the government for a
separate state in the north and east of the country since 1983.
</P>
