<HEADLINE> Brazil's Coffee Crop to Rise 23 Percent </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BRASILIA, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Brazil's 1998-99 coffee
harvest will total 34.55 million 60-kilo bags, a 23 percent
increase over the previous year's 28 million bag harvest.
</P>
<P>
Industry, Commerce and Tourism Minister Jose Botafogo Goncalves
said on Monday that coffee exports next year would be valued at
2.1 billion U.S. dollars, a 9.3 percent drop over 1998's 2.4
billion dollars, due to the collapse of prices on world markets.
</P>
<P>
Botafogo predicted that Brazil's 1999-2000 coffee harvest would
drop 33 percent to 23.15 million 60-kilo bags, due to high
temperatures and scarce rains in the states of Espirito Santo and
Bahia.
</P>
<P>
Brazil is the world's largest coffee producer and exporter.
</P>
