"Xinhua Daily Telegraph"
</P>
<P>
-- Leading Chinese officials on Monday visited an exhibition
commemorating the 20th anniversary of the 3rd Plenary Session of
the 11th Central Committee of the Communist Party of China (CPC).
</P>
<P>
They included Wei Jianxing, member of the Standing Committee of
the Political Bureau of the CPC Central Committee, and Li Lanqing,
also member of the Standing Committee of the Political Bureau of
the CPC Central Committee and vice-premier,
</P>
<P>
The exhibition, which opened on December 15, includes some 40
photos, more than 200 commemorative objects, as well as a number
of models and charts.
</P>
<P>
-- There was a quiet cremation in Beijing yesterday for Qian
Zhongshu who passed away two days ago, and who is regarded as one
of China's greatest writers and scholars of this century. His
novel "The Besieged City" is quite popular both at home and abroad.
</P>
<P>
 "China Daily"
</P>
<P>
-- China will launch a nationwide comprehensive investigation
of land, oceanic and mineral resources, beginning next year.
</P>
<P>
-- The Ministry of Civil Affairs has dispatched seven work
teams of senior officials to inspect areas hard hit in this
summer's floods in an effort to secure a comfortable winter and
cozy new year for millions of flood-affected people, ministry
officials said. 
</P>
