<BODY>
<HEADLINE> Villa Move Back to Top of English Premier League </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Aston Villa moved back to the
top of the English Premier League when an own goal helped Villa a
crucial 1-0 win over Charlton Athletic on Monday.
</P>
<P>
Unlucky defender Richard Rufus set up the visitors victory at
the Valley with a third minute deflection that condemned
struggling Charlton to a fifth successive defeat.
</P>
<P>
England international Dion Dublin pulled the ball back across
the goal from the right side of the box, the ball hitting Rufus
and rebounding into the net past goalkeeper Sasa Ilic.
</P>
<P>
Charlton came close to equalising after the interval when
Villa fullback Alan Wright had to sweep hurriedly off the line,
his clearance setting up a good chance at the other end.
</P>
<P>
Ilic kept Charlton in the game in the second half with a
crucial diving block from Julian Joachim who later had the ball
in the net only to be ruled offside.
</P>
<P>
Villa goalkeeper Michael Oakes also pulled off a brilliant
save from Neil Redfearn in the 80th minute, diving instinctively
to push the goalbound ball over the bar. Seconds later Charlton's
Danny Mills hit the bar.
</P>
<P>
If the manner of victory was unexpected for a team boasting
some prolific scorers, it was in keeping with a match that was
held up at halftime by a bizarre search for a fourth official
from among the watching crowd.
</P>
<P>
The second half started 15 minutes late after the referee
pulled a hamstring and had to be replaced by the fourth man, who
had no immediate backup.
</P>
<P>
A qualified official was eventually found amongst the
spectators. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> XIE19981222.0275 </DOCNO>
<DATE_TIME> 1998-12-22 </DATE_TIME>
