<HEADLINE> Hungary Keeps Strong Economic Growth in 1998 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
BUDAPEST, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Hungary recorded a 5.1
percent gross domestic product (GDP) growth in the first three
quarters of 1998.
</P>
<P>
Growth in the third quarter retained its momentum in the first
half of the year, soaring 5.6 percent over the same period of last
year, while GDP in the first half increased 4.8 percent over the
corresponding period of last year, showed figures released Monday
by the Central Bureau of Statistics.
</P>
<P>
Industrial production kept growing in the year with a 12.8
percent growth registered in the first nine months. Domestic
investment rose 14 percent in the same period.
</P>
<P>
Exports growth and expanding residents consumption also
contributed to the overall GDP growth. 
</P>
