<HEADLINE> Zidane Scoops Top Awards </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
LONDON, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Zinedine Zidane, who led
France to win the World Cup last summer, was voted European
footballer of the year.
</P>
<P>
The Juventus midfielder topped the poll ahead of two other
world cup stars, Croatian Davor Suker and Brazilian Ronaldo.
</P>
<P>
It completed an award winning Monday for the player, who was
also voted Reuters sports personality of the year.
</P>
<P>
His two goal performance in the World Cup final was perhaps
the most significant single contribution during the entire
football year and these awards reflect that.
</P>
<P>
But Zidane's prominent role in France's success was made all
the more extraordinary because of his red card in the earlier
stages of the competition.
</P>
<P>
In addition to his international success, Zidane was also a vit
al member of the Juventus side who won the Italian Serie A title
and reached the final of the European Champions league. 
