<HEADLINE> U.S. Stocks Extend Gains </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
NEW YORK, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Share prices on Wall Street
rose Monday, with the Dow Jones industrial average up 85.22 to
8,988.85, according to preliminary figures.
</P>
<P>
The technology-heavy Nasdaq composite index rose a staggering
51.89 points to a record of 2,138.03, breaking Friday's record.
The Standard &AMP; Poor's 500 rose 14.81 to 1,202.84, also a record
high.
</P>
<P>
Computer and other technology stocks, such as Dow component IBM
and Nasdaq's Dell, pushed major market indicators up.
</P>
<P>
Investors have been psychologically prepared for events such as
the impeachment of President Clinton in the House and U.S.-British
military strikes against Iraq so that these events little affected
the market, analysts said.
</P>
<P>
Market players did not hold a wait and see attitude toward
Tuesday's decision-making Fed meeting as they do not see the
possibility of a further interest cut as imminent when the
economic situation is stable and there is no urgent need to
stimulate the market through such a move.
</P>
<P>
On the New York Stock Exchange, advancers led decliners 5-4,
with trading volume totaling 742 million shares, against 835
million previously. 
</P>
</TEXT>
