<HEADLINE> IDB Helps Private Sector Development in Latin America </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
WASHINGTON, December 21 (Xinhua) -- The Inter-American
Development Bank (IDB) Monday announced the approval of a 75
million U.S. dollar loan to the Darby LAMF, an emerging markets
fund for financing infrastructure projects in Latin America and the
Caribbean.
</P>
<P>
The fund will provide a type of financing -- mezzanine
financing, combining debt and equity features, that has not been
generally available in Latin America.
</P>
<P>
The IDB support for the fund will help catalyze private sector
investment in such infrastructure sectors as water,
transportation, power and telecommunications.
</P>
<P>
This is the IDB's first loan to a private sector fund. 
</P>
</TEXT>
