<HEADLINE> Sudanese Parliament Speaker Resigns </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
KHARTOUM, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Sudanese National Assembly
(parliament) accepted the resignation of the powerful Speaker,
Hassan Abdulla al Turabi, at a session Monday.
</P>
<P>
At the session, Turabi, who is considered to be the power
behind Sudan's government, said that the purpose of his
resignation is to pave the way for a multi-party mechanism in the
country.
</P>
<P>
Turabi had expressed earlier that he intended to resign as the
speaker and to take up the post of General Secretary of the ruling
National Congress, which will be formally registered as a party in
January next year.
</P>
<P>
Earlier Monday, Deputy Committee of the parliament voiced the
hope that Turabi can serve out his remaining tenure, which expires
in 2000.
</P>
<P>
The National Assembly is the first Sudanese parliament that was
formed by a general election in 1995. 
</P>
</TEXT>
