<HEADLINE> Xinhua Mideast News Summary at 21:10 GMT, December 21 </HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
ANKARA -- Turkish Prime Minister designate Bulent Ecevit
announced Monday that he had returned his mandate for a government
formation to President Suleyman Demirel.
</P>
<P>
Ecevit, also leader of the Democratic Left Party (DSP), the
fourth biggest party in the parliament, was assigned by Demirel to
form the 56th coalition government on December 2 after the former
minority government led by Mesut Yilmaz collapsed for his
corruption scandals on November 25. (BC-Turkey-Government)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
CAIRO -- Egypt has accused Richard Butler, the chief
U.N. weapons inspector in Iraq, of being a troublemaker and asked
him to quit.
</P>
<P>
Foreign Minister Amr Moussa said Sunday that it is in the
interest of all that Butler's mission would come to an end.
(BC-Egypt-Butler-Criticism)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD -- Iraqi President Saddam Hussein on Monday chaired a
meeting attended by several members of the Revolutionary Command
Council and the ruling Baath party, the Iraqi News Agency
reported.
</P>
<P>
This was the first time Saddam chaired a meeting since the
four-day U.S.-British air strikes against Iraq came to an end on
Sunday. No detail of the meeting is available. (BC-Iraq-Saddam)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- The Israeli Knesset (parliament) passed its first
reading Monday of the bill abolishing direct election of prime
minister.
</P>
<P>
The bill was passed by a vote of 62 - 54 in the first reading.
It will be sent back to the Knesset Law Committee for preparations
for its second and thrid readings in the Knesset.
(BC-Israel-Knesset)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
BAGHDAD, December 21 (Xinhua) -- Iraqi Deputy Prime Minister
Tariq Aziz called the U.S.-British air strikes against Iraq as a
"criminal aggression" aimed at bringing country back to the
pre-industrial age.
</P>
<P>
As to the casualties of the army, he said that 62 died and 180
injured.
</P>
<P>
However, he did not give the exact figure of civilian
casualties, saying the damage was similar to that in the 1991 Gulf
War and the almost all the industrial sites were pounded.
</P>
<P>
He said the U.S. and Britain targeted civilian and government
buildings, radio and TV facilities, communication institutions,
hospitals and schools. (BC-Iraq-Aziz)
</P>
<P>
- - - -
</P>
<P>
JERUSALEM -- Israeli Knesset (parliament) Monday passed a bill
calling for early elections, dissolving the legislative body.
</P>
<P>
The bill was passed in the first reading by a vote of 81-30,
with 4 abstentions. Two more readings are required for final
approval. (BC-Israel-Parliament) 
</P>
